This paper deals with the problem of size discovery in radio networks, which is a topic related to network communication and information theory. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the study of graph properties and algorithms, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the use of labels and the analysis of their length could be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
